    <div align="left" id="post_message_45202">Let me start by saying I never played DnD, ever.<br />
<br />
Earlier today I picked up NWN and fired it up. Problem is, I have no friggin idea how the damage on the weapons work because I never had an prior knowledge of it, and they dont explain it in the game.<br />
<br />
I'm pretty sure it has something to do with rolling a dice, but I have no idea.<br />
<br />
Could someone quickly explain to me or point me to a DnD for Dummies website? I downloaded the FAQ for 3rd edition rules from wizards of the coast but it answers advanced questions, not the basics   ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />
Bon·do·ri<br />
adj.        <br />
1. Deviating from what is ordinary, usual, or expected; strange or peculiar.<br />
2. Random and unusual death to sea turtles.<br />
