    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_45211">Depends what you are facing.  2h gives you a hard hit, good for overcoming damage resistance or doing the max damage on attacks of opportunity.  Sword and Board style gives you the best defense.  Both are equally accurate (the 1.5x str bonus thing for 2h only applies on damage, not to hit).  But if you don't need those things, dual wield does the most damage.  Especially when wielding 2 weapons that have additional bonus damage like +1d6 fire. </div>
