    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_45212">The problem with dual wield is its cost in feats only to put it on par with wielding a two hander in damage, and sometimes less.  <br />
<br />
Two feats minimum for dual wield, three for improved dual wield.  Four to use a double axe or double sword.  With two feats you could get improved critical and weapon focus, a third would get you weapon spec or knockdown.  <br />
<br />
The -2 to hit on each attack is pretty severe against tough opponents.  Against easy opponents dual wield outdamages single wielding, but all it does is kill opponents that you could've killed easily anyway, just faster. <br />
<br />
The best use of dual wield is actually with the finesse fighter, I have found.  Using two of the same weapon, weapon focus, spec and improved critical, and not really having the opportunity to use two weapons or larger weapons effectively, the finesse fighter gets a very high AC and one of the best BABs.<br />
 </div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
